spanGrp.span: My grandmother came from Valle de la Estrella;
Ys mamita bet r (_) Valle de la Estrella
Valle de la Estrella is located in Talamanca;
My great-grandmothers name is Grandma Dominga;
ys bisabwela je kie Mamita Dominga
my grandmas name is Maria Josefa Obando.
ys mamita kie Maria Josefa Obando
She came from there, from Valle de la Estrella, from a place called Talamanca.
je bet r jega Valle de la Estrella jam k' Talamanka
And my grandpas name is Rafael Fernandez.
Jem (_) (_) ys tatiga kie r Rafael Fernandes
They came from that area too, from a place called San Jose Cabecar.
je bet r jam je wa b jie-wa bet (_) sa k' juei wa k' kie San Jos Kabkar
Je wa ys mamita de r
and so they left their homeland, came out of the mountains [and made it down here].
(_) (extra) (_) (_) Je wa jie-wa des-lo r k'bata jrga jie-wa des-lo r k'bata jrga
There is a road in the mountains, used by the ancestors long ago.
Je wa ala kablali jen r sigegl-wa shk-gl r Jen r sigegl-wa shk-gl r '_jira k'bata n
Then we thus grew up around here; we are their grandchildren and we speak our language.
Jemra n n jera jebi sa kibin' jiwa Sa r tachi-wa Sa sa t'-g se kt' jem jie-wa de-lo-te je wa
We work here and we grew up here in Ujarraz.
Sa shkabl-g jiska sa kebir-g r jiska Ujarras
We all belong to the same clan.
sa r dits'-wa sa r mismo
Most of our relatives live there, in Talamanca;
Sa yaiwa kebiye ts r je wa jam Talamanka (_) Je wa
they are there and we are here.
jie-wa ts jiwa sa ts jebi sa dam-lo pe shan
We all work and grew up;
our great-grandparents, our children in law, our parents in law, and our grandchildren are many, not a few.
Jebi sa yaiwa r t Sa sa (r) sa kla-wa sa db-wa sa nwagi-wa sa tachi-wa je r t Ka r jjngla un
Je t k' je k r k' klabe k
We do not lose our Sk language;
Ka sa t Sk kt' she-w ta (m)
we always speak it.We will never lose it.
(_) sa t'-g (_) r (m) Ka sa w je shew-n ta nunka un
My father weaves baskets and calabashes very well.
S-kaga t jaba yue kokbl yue tara b k
My mother is ill now, but she used to prepare chicha and the porridge very well.
Ys mina dwraw jira (_) mama t b (_) di ble di ble bokor bi-g jir w-g k barama
We will not forget our language;
Ka sa shen ka sa sk kt' she-n
we will maintain it till we die.
sa jr n nunka asta sa dua-w jen kea sa t sk kt' shew-w (r) shew-w
We are not going to lose it just like that.
There used to be a lot of thing to eat in the mountains, but not anymore.
_ji sigegl/ jiskara t jir ts t k'bata n (_) kata-n bi jira ka je ta
Nowadays the place looks very different.
The river flooded our entire place;
jirda digl (r) digl w k' menets-m kable
the whites change the course of the road.
Ka sa je/ala (_) yua-n jaule yugsuwa t
Now there are lots of whites around here.
in our language we call them Spanish;
(_) Se je kt' wa se je t kie r sikwa
jie-wa/ sigegl-wa t (_) kie r yugsuwa
Thats how you say it in our language.
jebi se je kt wa kie r
They have many tractors, but we dont.
Pero (_) jie-wa ts t tebeli_yaga ta jir ta Ka sa je w ta
Long ago we used to live differently;
jra se je ser-g r jaule
They were of wood and palm leaves.
se je j r kal se j r skk' uluk'
Now people have made nice houses with many other materials and stuff.
